# Fishmarket v3 – Data

## Firestore

**Partial updates and `undefined`**: Firestore's `updateDoc()` does not accept `undefined` as a field value (it throws). The client uses an internal helper `omitUndefined()` in `src/lib/firestore.ts` to strip any keys with `undefined` before calling `updateDoc`. Callers of `updateUserProfile` (and any other update helpers that use it) can safely pass partial objects with optional fields set to `undefined`; only defined fields are written. To remove a field, use Firestore's `deleteField()` or omit the key.

### `users` collection

Stores user profiles. Document ID = Firebase Auth `uid`. Created on sign-up.

**Document shape** (matches `UserProfile` type in `src/lib/firestore.ts`):

| Field | Type | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `uid` | `string` | Firebase Auth UID (same as doc ID) |
| `email` | `string` | User's email address |
| `displayName` | `string` | Optional display name |
| `username` | `string` | Optional unique handle (shown as @username) |
| `location` | `string` | Optional (e.g. "Stockholm Sweden") |
| `bio` | `string` | Optional, max 500 chars |
| `avatarUrl` | `string \| null` | Optional profile image URL (Firebase Storage `users/{uid}/avatar.ext`) |
| `followerCount` | `number` | Optional. Displayed on profile (e.g. "300 Follower"). |
| `tiktokUrl` | `string` | Optional. TikTok profile URL; shown as social link on profile. |
| `youtubeUrl` | `string` | Optional. YouTube channel URL; shown as social link on profile. |
| `instagramUrl` | `string` | Optional. Instagram profile URL; shown as social link on profile. |
| `isSeller` | `boolean` | Whether the user is a seller (default false). Sellers appear in Top Brands and Brand Suggestions on the buyer dashboard. |
| `stripeAccountId` | `string` | Optional. Stripe Connect account ID (sellers). Created during Stripe Connect onboarding. |
| `stripeCustomerId` | `string` | Optional. Stripe Customer ID (buyers). Created on first purchase. |
| `stripeOnboardingComplete` | `boolean` | Optional. `true` once Stripe Connect KYC is verified. Sellers cannot receive purchases until this is `true`. |
| `createdAt` | `Timestamp` | Server timestamp |

**Helpers**:

- `createUserProfile(uid, email, displayName?, isSeller?)` — `src/lib/firestore.ts` — creates user doc with `setDoc` (uses uid as doc ID)
- `getUserProfile(uid)` — `src/lib/firestore.ts` — get user doc by uid
- `updateUserProfile(uid, data)` — `src/lib/firestore.ts` — partial update on `users/{uid}`; strips `undefined` via `omitUndefined` before writing
- `getSellers(limitCount?)` — `src/lib/firestore.ts` — query users where `isSeller == true`
- `uploadAvatar(file, uid)` — `src/lib/storage.ts` — uploads to `users/{uid}/avatar.{ext}`, returns download URL

### `listings` collection

Stores product listings. Schema defined in `src/lib/schemas/listing.ts`.

**Document shape** (matches `Listing` type):

| Field | Type | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `title` | `string` | Product title |
| `description` | `string` | Optional description |
| `specifications` | `string` | Optional specifications text |
| `price` | `number` | Price amount |
| `shippingCost` | `number` | Optional shipping cost |
| `currency` | `string` | Default "SEK" |
| `condition` | `"new" \| "used" \| "refurbished"` | Product condition |
| `category` | `string` | Category (e.g. Lures, Rods) |
| `fishType` | `string` | Fish type (e.g. Perch, Pike) |
| `variants` | `VariantGroup[]` | Optional variant groups. Each group has `values: VariantValue[]` where each value has `id`, `name`, `price`, `available`, and optional `imageUrl` |
| `imageUrls` | `string[]` | URLs from Firebase Storage |
| `createdAt` | `Timestamp` | Server timestamp |
| `sellerId` | `string` | Firebase Auth UID of the listing creator |

**Helpers** (in `src/lib/`):

- `createListing(data)` — `src/lib/firestore.ts` — adds doc to `listings`, returns doc id
- `updateListing(listingId, data)` — `src/lib/firestore.ts` — partial update
- `getListing(id)` — `src/lib/firestore.ts` — fetches a single listing by ID
- `getListings()` — `src/lib/firestore.ts` — fetches all listings ordered by `createdAt` desc
- `getUserListings(uid)` — `src/lib/firestore.ts` — fetches listings for a seller, ordered by `createdAt` desc
- `uploadListingImages(files, listingId)` — `src/lib/storage.ts` — uploads to `listings/{listingId}/`, returns download URLs
- `uploadVariantImage(file, listingId, valueId)` — `src/lib/storage.ts` — uploads to `listings/{listingId}/variants/{valueId}.{ext}`, returns download URL
- `getNewReleases(limitCount?)` — `src/lib/firestore.ts` — newest listings ordered by `createdAt` desc
- `getListingsByFishType(fishType, limitCount?)` — `src/lib/firestore.ts` — listings filtered by fish type
- `searchListings(filters)` — `src/lib/firestore.ts` — search/filter listings. Accepts `ListingFilters`: `category`, `fishType`, `condition`, `sellerId` (Firestore `where`), plus `searchQuery`, `minPrice`, `maxPrice` (client-side). Returns `Listing[]`
- `getUserProfiles(uids)` — `src/lib/firestore.ts` — batch-fetch user profiles by UID array (groups of 10 for Firestore `in` limit). Returns `Map<string, UserProfile>`
- `getListingsByIds(ids)` — `src/lib/firestore.ts` — batch-fetch listings by ID array (groups of 10 for Firestore `in` limit). Returns `Map<string, Listing>`

### `orders` collection

Stores purchase orders. Schema defined in `src/lib/schemas/order.ts`. Created when a buyer purchases a listing.

**Document shape** (matches `Order` type):

| Field | Type | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `orderNumber` | `number` | Sequential display number (e.g. 1001) |
| `sellerId` | `string` | Seller's Firebase Auth UID |
| `buyerId` | `string` | Buyer's Firebase Auth UID |
| `buyerName` | `string` | Buyer display name (denormalized) |
| `buyerEmail` | `string` | Optional buyer email (for contact info in order details) |
| `listingId` | `string` | Reference to the purchased listing |
| `listingTitle` | `string` | Denormalized listing title |
| `quantity` | `number` | Number of items purchased |
| `unitPrice` | `number` | Price per item |
| `totalAmount` | `number` | Total order amount |
| `currency` | `string` | Default "SEK" |
| `status` | `OrderStatus` | One of: `pending`, `confirmed`, `shipped`, `delivered`, `needs_fulfillment`, `return_requested`, `returned`, `cancelled` |
| `trackingNumber` | `string` | Optional tracking number |
| `carrier` | `string` | Optional carrier name (e.g. "Postnord") |
| `shippingAddress` | `string` | Optional buyer shipping address |
| `stripeCheckoutSessionId` | `string` | Optional. Stripe Checkout Session ID. Set by webhook on order creation. |
| `stripePaymentIntentId` | `string` | Optional. Stripe PaymentIntent ID. Set by webhook on order creation. |
| `selectedVariantValueId` | `string` | Optional. ID of the `VariantValue` purchased. |
| `selectedVariantLabel` | `string` | Optional. Human-readable variant label, e.g. "Color: Red". |
| `createdAt` | `Timestamp` | Server timestamp |
| `updatedAt` | `Timestamp` | Server timestamp |

**Status → Badge mapping** (in `ORDER_STATUS_BADGE_VARIANT`):
- `pending`, `confirmed`, `cancelled` → **default** badge
- `shipped`, `delivered` → **success** badge
- `needs_fulfillment` → **warning** badge
- `return_requested`, `returned` → **error** badge

**Helpers** (in `src/lib/firestore.ts`):

- `createOrder(data)` — adds doc to `orders`, returns doc id
- `getSellerOrders(sellerId, limitCount?)` — query orders for a seller, ordered by `createdAt` desc
- `getBuyerOrders(buyerId, limitCount?)` — query orders for a buyer, ordered by `createdAt` desc
- `updateOrder(orderId, data)` — partial update (e.g. status change, adds `updatedAt`)
- `getOrdersByStatus(sellerId, status)` — filter orders by status

**API routes**:

- `GET /api/seller/analytics?sellerId=...` — server-side aggregation via Firebase Admin SDK. Returns `SellerAnalytics`: `earningBalance`, `lifetimeEarning`, `lastPayout`, `nextPayout`, `currency`, `totalOrders`, `shippedOrders`, `pendingOrders`.
- `POST /api/stripe/connect/onboard` — creates Stripe Connect Express account + Account Link URL for seller onboarding
- `GET /api/stripe/connect/status?uid=...` — checks Stripe Connect account verification status
- `POST /api/stripe/checkout` — creates Stripe Checkout Session with destination charge for buyer purchase
- `POST /api/stripe/webhook` — handles Stripe webhook events (order creation, status updates, stock deduction)

**React Query hooks** (in `src/hooks/`):

- `useSellerAnalytics(sellerId)` — fetches from the analytics API route
- `useSellerOrders(sellerId)` — fetches orders via Firestore client
- `useSellerInventory(sellerId)` — derives inventory from `getUserListings`

### `posts` collection

Stores video posts for the social feed. Schema defined in `src/lib/schemas/post.ts`.

**Document shape** (matches `Post` type):

| Field | Type | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `userId` | `string` | Firebase Auth UID of the post creator |
| `videoUrl` | `string` | Firebase Storage download URL (`posts/{postId}/video.{ext}`) |
| `thumbnailUrl` | `string` | Thumbnail JPEG URL (Firebase Storage `posts/{postId}/thumbnail.jpg`). Generated client-side from the video during post creation. |
| `caption` | `string` | Post caption (max 300 chars) |
| `hashtags` | `string[]` | Hashtag strings (e.g. `["#viral", "#fishing"]`). Predefined or user-entered. |
| `coverFrameColor` | `string \| null` | Hex color for decorative border/frame around the video in the feed. Null = no frame. |
| `taggedUserIds` | `string[]` | UIDs of tagged users (People/Creators selected in Tag & Link step). |
| `taggedListingIds` | `string[]` | IDs of tagged product listings (Products selected in Tag & Link step). |
| `visibility` | `string` | `"everyone"` \| `"followers"` \| `"friends"` \| `"only_me"`. Default `"everyone"`. |
| `allowComments` | `boolean` | Whether viewers can comment (default true). |
| `allowDuets` | `boolean` | Whether others can create duets (default true). |
| `allowDownload` | `boolean` | Whether viewers can download the video (default false). |
| `scheduledAt` | `number \| null` | Unix timestamp (ms) for scheduled publishing. Null = publish immediately. |
| `likeCount` | `number` | Denormalized like count |
| `saveCount` | `number` | Denormalized save count |
| `commentCount` | `number` | Denormalized comment count |
| `viewCount` | `number` | Denormalized view count (default 0, for future view tracking) |
| `createdAt` | `Timestamp` | Server timestamp |

**Constants** (in `src/lib/constants/post.ts`):

- `TRENDING_HASHTAGS` — predefined trending hashtag strings
- `COVER_FRAME_COLORS` — predefined cover frame color options (`{ id, label, hex }`)
- `VISIBILITY_OPTIONS` — visibility radio options (`{ id, label, description, icon, emoji }`)
- `INTERACTION_SETTINGS` — interaction toggle options (`{ id, label, description, icon, emoji, defaultValue }`)

**Helpers** (in `src/lib/firestore.ts`):

- `createPost(data)` — adds doc to `posts`, returns doc id. Accepts all new fields (hashtags, coverFrameColor, taggedUserIds, taggedListingIds, visibility, interaction toggles, scheduledAt).
- `getPost(id)` — fetches a single post by ID
- `getFeedPosts(limitCount?, afterDoc?)` — paginated feed, `createdAt` desc. Returns `{ posts, lastDoc }`
- `togglePostLike(postId, userId)` — toggle like (add/remove `post_likes` doc, increment/decrement `likeCount`), returns new liked state
- `togglePostSave(postId, userId)` — same for saves
- `getUserPostInteractions(postIds, userId)` — batch check liked/saved states for feed rendering
- `getUserPosts(userId, limitCount?)` — query posts by userId, ordered by `createdAt` desc. Used in profile "My videos" tab
- `getTaggedPosts(userId, limitCount?)` — query posts where `taggedUserIds` array-contains userId, ordered by `createdAt` desc. Used in profile "Tagged" tab
- `getUserLikedPosts(userId, limitCount?)` — query `post_likes` by userId, batch-fetch corresponding posts. Used in profile "Like" tab
- `getUserSavedPosts(userId, limitCount?)` — query `post_saves` by userId, batch-fetch corresponding posts. Used in profile "Favorites" tab
- `addComment(postId, userId, text)` — adds doc to `post_comments`, increments `commentCount`. Returns comment ID
- `getPostComments(postId, limitCount?)` — query comments for a post, ordered by `createdAt` desc. Returns `PostComment[]`
- `deleteComment(commentId, postId)` — deletes the comment doc, decrements `commentCount`
- `searchUsers(query)` — fetch users, client-side filter by `displayName`/`username`. Used in Tag & Link step.
- `uploadPostVideo(file, postId)` — `src/lib/storage.ts` — uploads to `posts/{postId}/video.{ext}`, returns download URL
- `uploadPostThumbnail(blob, postId)` — `src/lib/storage.ts` — uploads a JPEG Blob to `posts/{postId}/thumbnail.jpg`, returns download URL
- `generateVideoThumbnail(file)` — `src/lib/video.ts` — captures a frame from a video File via off-screen `<video>` + `<canvas>`, returns a JPEG Blob (480px wide, aspect-ratio preserved)

### `post_likes` collection

Tracks which users liked which posts. Document ID = `{postId}_{userId}`.

| Field | Type | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `postId` | `string` | Reference to post |
| `userId` | `string` | User who liked |
| `createdAt` | `Timestamp` | When liked |

### `post_saves` collection

Tracks which users saved which posts. Same shape as `post_likes`.

| Field | Type | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `postId` | `string` | Reference to post |
| `userId` | `string` | User who saved |
| `createdAt` | `Timestamp` | When saved |

### `post_comments` collection

Stores comments on posts. Document ID = auto-generated.

| Field | Type | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `postId` | `string` | Reference to post |
| `userId` | `string` | User who commented |
| `text` | `string` | Comment text |
| `createdAt` | `Timestamp` | When commented |

### `save_collections` collection

Stores user-created save collections (folders/boards for organizing saved posts). Schema defined in `src/lib/schemas/collection.ts`.

| Field | Type | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `userId` | `string` | Owner's Firebase Auth UID |
| `name` | `string` | Collection name |
| `createdAt` | `Timestamp` | When created |
| `updatedAt` | `Timestamp` | When last modified |

**Helpers** (in `src/lib/firestore.ts`):

- `createSaveCollection(userId, name)` — creates doc, returns ID
- `getUserCollections(userId)` — query by userId, ordered by `createdAt` desc
- `updateSaveCollection(collectionId, data)` — partial update (name)
- `deleteSaveCollection(collectionId)` — deletes collection + all its `collection_items`

### `collection_items` collection

Tracks which posts are in which collections. Document ID = `{collectionId}_{postId}` (prevents duplicates).

| Field | Type | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `collectionId` | `string` | Reference to `save_collections` doc |
| `postId` | `string` | Reference to post |
| `userId` | `string` | Owner (denormalized for queries) |
| `createdAt` | `Timestamp` | When saved |

**Helpers** (in `src/lib/firestore.ts`):

- `getCollectionItems(collectionId, limitCount?)` — items in a collection, ordered by `createdAt` desc
- `getCollectionItemPostIds(collectionId)` — lightweight variant returning just post IDs
- `getPostCollectionIds(postId, userId)` — which collections contain the post (for SaveDrawer checkboxes)
- `savePostToCollection(postId, collectionId, userId)` — add to collection + ensure `post_saves` doc + increment `saveCount` if first save
- `removePostFromCollection(postId, collectionId, userId)` — remove from collection + cleanup `post_saves` + decrement `saveCount` if no collections remain

### User profile (for Firebase Auth / Firestore)

Profile fields used on the profile page and Edit Bio form are defined in **`src/lib/schemas/profile.ts`**. When tying to Firebase, store per user (e.g. `users/{uid}` or `profiles/{uid}`):

| Field | Type | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `displayName` | `string` | Display name |
| `username` | `string` | Unique handle (shown as @username) |
| `location` | `string` | Optional (e.g. "Stockholm Sweden") |
| `bio` | `string` | Optional, max 500 chars |
| `avatarUrl` | `string \| null` | Optional profile image URL (e.g. Storage) |
| `isSeller` | `boolean` | Whether the user is a seller (default false) |
| `followerCount` | `number` | Optional; can be computed from a subcollection |
| `createdAt` / `updatedAt` | `Timestamp` | Optional server timestamps |
